d_km2          = 3824 \n|area_water_km2         =\n|area_water_percent     = \n|area_urban_km2         = 1073\n|area_metro_km2         = 1073\n|population_as_of       =2010\n|population_footnotes   = \n|population_note        = \n|population_total       =1,854,510\n|population_density_km2 = auto\n|population_metro       = 893,550\n|population_density_metro_km2 =\n|population_urban       = 893,550\n|population_density_urban_km2 =\n|timezone = [[China Standard Time|China Standard]]\n|utc_offset = +8\n|coor_pinpoint = Pingxiang government\n|coordinates            = {{coord|27.659|N|113.887|E|type:adm2nd_region:CN-36_source:Gaode|format=dms|display=it}}\n|elevation_footnotes    =  <!--for references: use <ref> </ref> tags-->\n|elevation_m              = \n|elevation_ft           = \n|postal_code_type       =  <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n|postal_code            = 337000\n|area_code              = 0799\n|iso_code = [[ISO 3166-2:CN|CN-JX-03]]\n|website = {{URL|www.pingxiang.gov.cn/}}\n|footnotes              = \n}}\n\n'''Pingxiang''' ({{zh|s=\u840d\u4e61 |t=\u840d\u9109 |p=P\u00edngxi\u0101ng|w=P'ing-hsiang}}) is a medium-sized [[prefecture-level city]] located in western [[Jiangxi]] province, People's Republic of China.\n\n==Geography and climate==\n\nPingxiang is a limitrophe city between Jiangxi and [[Hunan]] provinces. Approximately 110 kilometers from [[Changsha]], [[Hunan]], about 260 kilometers from [[Nanchang]].  Most of the area around the city is hilly and mountainous, although the city itself is relatively flat. As a sub-tropical climatic city, Pingxiang has mild winters, long and hot summers, with plenty of rainfall. The annual average temperature is 18&nbsp;\u00b0C.\n\n{{Weather box|width=auto\n|metric first=y\n|single line=y \n|collapsed = Y\n|location = Pingxiang (1981\u20132010 normals)\n|Jan high C =  9.3\n|Feb high C = 11.6\n|Mar high C = 15.7\n|Apr high C = 22.5\n|May high C = 27.6\n|Jun high C = 30.5\n|Jul high C = 34.2\n|Aug high C = 33.4\n|Sep high C = 29.4\n|Oct high C = 24.3\n|Nov high C = 18.5\n|Dec high C = 12.6\n\n|Jan mean C =  5.5\n|Feb mean C =  7.7\n|Mar mean C = 11.4\n|Apr mean C = 17.6\n|May mean C = 22.5\n|Jun mean C = 25.8\n|Jul mean C = 29.0\n|Aug mean C = 28.0\n|Sep mean C = 24.3\n|Oct mean C = 19.0\n|Nov mean C = 13.2\n|Dec mean C =  7.6\n\n|Jan low C =  2.9\n|Feb low C =  5.0\n|Mar low C =  8.4\n|Apr low C = 14.1\n|May low C = 18.7\n|Jun low C = 22.3\n|Jul low C = 24.8\n|Aug low C = 24.3\n|Sep low C = 20.7\n|Oct low C = 15.3\n|Nov low C =  9.5\n|Dec low C =  4.2\n|Jan record high C = 25.8 |Jan record low C = \u22123.9\n|Feb record high C = 30.5 |Feb record low C = \u22123.9\n|Mar record high C = 35.0 |Mar record low C = \u22121.7\n|Apr record high C = 35.7 |Apr record low C =  1.5\n|May record high C = 37.3 |May record low C =  9.0\n|Jun record high C = 37.6 |Jun record low C = 13.4\n|Jul record high C = 40.1 |Jul record low C = 17.4\n|Aug record high C = 41.0 |Aug record low C = 18.1\n|Sep record high C = 39.2 |Sep record low C = 12.6\n|Oct record high C = 35.9 |Oct record low C =  2.7\n|Nov record high C = 31.8 |Nov record low C = \u22121.1\n|Dec record high C = 25.5 |Dec record low C = \u22129.3\n|precipitation colour = green\n|Jan precipitation mm =  83.5\n|Feb precipitation mm = 108.3\n|Mar precipitation mm = 178.5\n|Apr precipitation mm = 204.0\n|May precipitation mm = 221.1\n|Jun precipitation mm = 238.2\n|Jul precipitation mm = 150.1\n|Aug precipitation mm = 132.9\n|Sep precipitation mm =  85.1\n|Oct precipitation mm =  81.2\n|Nov precipitation mm =  83.7\n|Dec precipitation mm =  58.2\n\n|Jan humidity = 84\n|Feb humidity = 84\n|Mar humidity = 84\n|Apr humidity = 83\n|May humidity = 82\n|Jun humidity = 83\n|Jul humidity = 77\n|Aug humidity = 80\n|Sep humidity = 80\n|Oct humidity = 79\n|Nov humidity = 79\n|Dec humidity = 80\n|source 1 = [http://data.cma.cn/data/weatherBk.html China Meteorological Data Service Center]\n}}\n\n==History==\nArchaeological evidence suggests that Pingxiang was first settled during the [[Stone Age]]. During the [[Han dynasty]], it was part of [[Yichun, Jiangxi|Yichun]]. In 267, during the time of the [[Three Kingdoms]], it became Pingxiang County, which made it a higher level of administration than what it is today. During the [[Tang Dynasty]] (618-907), it was part of the [[Jiangnanxi Circuit]], and was called [[Yuanzhou (modern Jiangxi)|Yuanzhou]]. Its name and area of administration were changed many times until 1970, when it assumed its present form.\n\n==Administration==\n\nPingxiang has direct jurisdiction over two [[Urban district (Great Britain and Ireland)|urban districts]], one economic development area, three [[County (People's Republic of China)|counties]], 28 towns, 18 townships, and 7 sub-districts.\n\n'''Urban districts''': \n*[[Anyuan District]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u5b89\u6e90\u533a}})\n*[[Xiangdong District]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u6e58\u4e1c\u533a}})\n*[[Anyuan Economic Development Zone]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u5b89\u6e90\u7ecf\u6d4e\u5f00\u53d1\u533a}})\n\n'''Counties''':\n*[[Shangli County]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u4e0a\u6817\u53bf}})\n*[[Luxi County, Jiangxi|Luxi County]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u82a6\u6eaa\u53bf}})\n*[[Lianhua County]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u83b2\u82b1\u53bf}})\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n!colspan=\"6\"| Map\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"11\"| <div style=\"position: relative\" class=\"center\">\n{{Image label begin|image=Administrative Division Pingxiang.png|width=300|link=}} \n{{Image label|x=290|y=450|scale=300/750|text=[[Anyuan District|'''Anyuan''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=90|y=580|scale=300/750|text=[[Xiangdong District|'''Xiangdong''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=240|y=240|scale=300/750|text=[[Shangli County|'''Shangli<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=500|y=500|scale=300/750|text=[[Luxi County, Jiangxi|'''Luxi<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=340|y=870|scale=300/750|text=[[Lianhua County|'''Lianhua<br>County''']]}}\n|}\n\n==Demographics==\nThe population of the total administrative area of Pingxiang was estimated to be 1,874,000 at the 2012 census.{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}\n\n==Economy==\n\nIn 2013, the [[GDP]] was 79.2 billion RMB, an 8.2% growth over the previous year. Rural income was 11,100 RMB, a 10.5% growth over 2012 and urban income was 23,489 RMB, an 11% growth over 2012 (without regard to inflation).\n\n==Resources==\nPingxiang has abundant water and mineral resources. Five rivers flow across the land which delivers approximately 2.626 billion cubic meters per year. Coal, iron ore, limestone, kaolin and granite are the most abundant minerals of the city. Even today, the ''Pingxiangren'' or local people proudly refer to their city as the \"coal center of southern China.\"\n\n==Transportation==\nPingxiang is a regional hub for transportation. It is about 1.5 hrs drive to the CSX from downtown of Pingxiang. A couple of highways and the main rail line between Changsha and Nanchang run through the city. The city has had a high-speed railway since September 2014.\n\n==Tourism==\nWugong (also known as WooKong) mountain is a national well known place for tourism. It lies in the east of Pingxiang, 45 minutes from downtown. The highest altitude is 1,918 meters while the average altitude is about 1,500 meters. Most of the landscape remains virginal in despite of some necessary infrastructures that benefit tourists.\n\nYangqi mountain is famous for the religion of Buddhism, lies in north of Pingxiang, one hour's drive from downtown.\n\nNielongdong (also known as Sinful Dragon Cave) has a tale which refers to Chinese traditional religion and zodiac. This beautiful area is only twenty minutes north.\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Pingxiang, Jiangxi}}\n*[http://www.pingxiang.gov.cn/ Official website (Chinese)]\n\n{{Jiangxi topics}}\n{{Jiangxi}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities in Jiangxi]]\n[[Category:Prefecture-level divisions of Jiangxi]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the city in Jiangxi province|th